1. Template Literals + Expressions
a) "5 + 7 = 12"
console.log(`5 + 7 = ${5 + 7}`);

b) Multi-line string
const multiLine = `
Line 1
Line 2
Line 3
`;

c) Full name
const firstName = "John";
const lastName = "Doe";
console.log(`${firstName} ${lastName}`);

2. Arrow Functions & this
a) Convert to arrow
const square = n => n * n;

b) Why logs undefined?
const obj = {
  value: 50,
  test: () => console.log(this.value)
};
obj.test();


//Reason: Arrow functions do not have their own this.
They take this from the outer/global scope → which does not have value.
So it prints undefined.

c) Correct version
const obj = {
  value: 50,
  test() {
    console.log(this.value);
  }
};
obj.test();

3. Rest, Spread & Copying Objects
a) Shallow copy
const productCopy = { ...product };

b) Merge objects
const merged = { ...a, ...b };

c) maxValue(...nums)
const maxValue = (...nums) => Math.max(...nums);

4. Destructuring & Optional Chaining
a) Extract a and b
const [a, b] = arr;

b) Extract brand
const { brand } = laptop;

c) Safe access
console.log(info?.user?.name);


//Output: undefined

5. Scoping (let/var/const)
a) var
for (var i = 0; i < 3; i++) {}
console.log(i); // 3


//Reason: var is NOT block scoped.

b) let
for (let j = 0; j < 3; j++) {}
console.log(j); // ReferenceError


//Reason: let is block scoped.

c) Why const?

//Reason: Because const prevents reassignment, helping avoid accidental changes to values that should remain fixed.

6. Ternary Operator – Practice
a) Convert to ternary
speed = kmph > 60 ? "Fast" : "Normal";

b) Adult or Minor
const status = age >= 18 ? "Adult" : "Minor";

c) Positive / Zero / Negative
const result = n > 0 
  ? "Positive" 
  : n === 0 
    ? "Zero" 
    : "Negative";

7. Spread, Rest & Arrays
a) Add 4 and 5
const numsUpdated = [...nums, 4, 5];

b) Combine arrays
const combined = [...a, ...b];

c) printNames(...names)
const printNames = (...names) => names;

8. Object Destructuring & Shorthand
a) Destructure
const { id, status } = user;

b) Convert to shorthand
const id = 101;
const role = "admin";

const userObj = { id, role };

c) Object + method shorthand
const person = {
  name: "Sam",
  greet() {
    console.log("Hello");
  }
};

9. Template Literals (More Practice)
a) Today's date
console.log(`Today is: ${new Date().toDateString()}`);

b) Score message
const message = `Hello ${NAME}, your score is ${SCORE}/100`;

10. Arrow Function Shorthands
a) One-line addition
const add = (a, b) => a + b;

b) isAdult
const isAdult = age => age >= 18;

c) double
const double = n => n * 2;

11. Spread Operator (Arrays & Objects)
a) Clone array
const copy = [...arr];

b) Add 100 to beginning
const updated = [100, ...arr];

c) Merge + override
const mergedObj = { ...obj1, ...obj2, prop: "newValue" };

12. Optional Chaining (More Practice)
a) Access city
console.log(user?.address?.city);

b) Access job.title safely
console.log(user?.job?.title);


 //Output: prints undefined

c) Example preventing crash
const emp = { name: "Paul" };

console.log(emp.address?.street);  

//Output:
// without ?. → TypeError
// with ?. → undefined
